The students at Sherry Curtis School were able to vote for one or more events for their field day. Below are the top three choices. List the names of the choices from most popular to least popular, separated by commas.

\begin{tabular}{|c|c|c|c|} \hline
Event & Kickball & Picnic & Softball \\ \hline 
& & &\\[-1.5ex]
Fraction liking event & $\frac{11}{30}$ & $\frac{7}{20}$ & $\frac{5}{12}$ \\[1ex] \hline
\end{tabular}
inference:
1) Find the LCM of the denominators of the fractions: 
$$LCM(30,20,12)=60$$

2) Multiply each fraction by an appropriate form of 1 to get equivalent fractions with the same denominator: 
$$\frac{11}{30} = \frac{11\times2}{30\times2} = \frac{22}{60}$$

$$\frac{7}{20} = \frac{7\times3}{20\times3} = \frac{21}{60}$$

$$\frac{5}{12} = \frac{5\times5}{12\times5} = \frac{25}{60}$$

3) Now, we can compare the numerators of the equivalent fractions to determine the order of popularity: 
$$25 > 22 > 21$$

4) Therefore, from most popular to least popular, the events are:
**Final Answer: \\boxed{Softball, Kickball, Picnic}. I hope it is correct.**
